name: Vydubychi
description: Vydubychi metro station is my association with departure and arriving. It's always filled with people who just came to the city or on the way to leave it because of a bus station outside. By their look, their walk you can notice how they are in a different state  - concentrated on something else than us, usual bypassers. Each one of them has their own destination, story and path in which they are making a hundreds miles step. Shot on Kodak Portra 400 film with 1978 Canon AE-1 manual camera.
